nd categorical facts; call the real summary-generation model, then score factual consistency (e.g., extractor-based check against source facts) across repeated runs with an acceptance threshold for key-value correctness.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"A lower-level stubbed test would always pass and miss model-quality failures.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.77,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: end-to-end inbox delivery failures often appear only with real email transport/auth/recipient handling. REAL-INFRA: requires real networked email service and mailbox verification. MOCK-HIDE: mocked mail sender can pass while real SMTP/API rejects payload or recipient config. LLM-DEP: disqualified by behavior text; this behavior is delivery success, not model output quality. MULTI-STEP agent chain not required. ADVERSARIAL-CRITIQUE: if using a local in-process mail sink as acceptance criterion, Integration might be enough. TOP2-CONTRAST: System wins because real transport/inbox is the failure boundary; flip to Integration if acceptance target is only internal handoff to a mail client interface.","test_description":"Execute the script in a test environment against reachable data sources and real email delivery infrastructure to a seeded test inbox; assert message arrival, recipient list correctness, and report body presence/format.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Real inbox delivery cannot be validated reliably with in-process fakes.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.14,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: real unreachable-service behavior plus persistence/retry across runs can fail in ways mocks hide (connection errors, retry timing/state). REAL-INFRA: includes network-unreachable mail service behavior and filesystem persistence across executions. MOCK-HIDE: mocked sender may not reproduce real exception classes/backoff paths. LLM-DEP: disqualified by behavior text; requirement is delivery fallback/retry mechanics. MULTI-STEP: not multi-agent reasoning; it is operational retry workflow. REJECTION-GATE for Integration: behavior text explicitly requires unreachable delivery service and next scheduled run retry, which can depend on real infra behavior. ADVERSARIAL-CRITIQUE: if retry logic is purely internal and triggered by injected errors, Integration may suffice. TOP2-CONTRAST: System wins because true outage + cross-run persistence is the failure boundary; flip to Integration if scheduler and mail errors are fully simulated but proven equivalent to production semantics.","test_description":"Force real mail endpoint unreachability (e.g., blackholed test SMTP/API), run report job and verify fallback file is written; restore mail service, trigger next scheduled execution, and verify prior report is retried and delivered exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Behavior explicitly depends on outage and retry across runs; lower levels risk missing real transport/state defects.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.27,"System":0.62,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
